Feedback

A lot of main components in the website hindered the branding of the company. It is important to make sure the uniformity of the website did not lose the attraction of our audience. Feedback that was given from the team included: inconsistent color pallete, poor mobile UX design, and lack of performance to excel other companies.

Organize

Prior research was implemeneted within the design to provide inspiration for the revamped website. The layout of the website catered towards the most important information our audience would mostly seek out for. The User Experience was also improved by providing more interative designs and concepts. The overall mood of the design greatly improved to make DinoDoods a fun and friendly brand.

Develop

The last step was to develop the revamped design using React. Since the old development was created with React and Tailwind, it allowed room for expanding my knowledge on front-end development. Mobile functionality greatly improved throughout the development process.

Conclusion

This project challenged my development, design, and analyitical skills. Taking initiative was the first step into rebuilding and rebranding DinoDood's website. I was able to take on multiple tasks with the best quality of work while maintaining company deadlines. Eventhough I lacked React experience, I finished with obtaining great foundational skills. The experience I gained can further provide amazing impacts for future projects and companies.
